properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 3 at 4:59AM AKST until January 5 at 9:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills ranging from
40 to 50 below zero.

* WHERE...Thompson Pass.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to 9 AM AKST Sunday. Temperatures
will warm and winds will relax some during the day Saturday
allowing conditions to improve. However, falling temperatures
and stronger winds will return overnight Saturday into Sunday
morning.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 5 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 9 AM AKST SUNDAY THROUGH THOMPSON PASS
